<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The function OS_FileSys_FindVirtMountPoint takes a non-const pointer parameter void *ref but only reads from it as a string (const char *target = (const char *)ref). At the call site OS_FileSysStatVolume passes a const char *name cast to void * ((void *)name), which discards the const qualifier. According to MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13, the pointer should point to a const-qualified type whenever possible. Declaring the parameter as const void *ref (and removing the const cast at the call site) would conform to the rule.
</scenario>
